heading.title: Annual dividends to be paid by public authorities to Consolidated Fund

p.emphasis: BE IT ENACTED by the Queen's Most Excellent Majesty by and with the advice and consent of the Legislative Council and the Legislative Assembly of Victoria in this present Parliament assembled and by the authority of the same as follows (that is to say):

doc:metadata.currencyStatement: Consolidated as in force on 1 July 2007

legis:body.p: This Act may be cited as the Public Authorities (Dividends) Act 1983.

The several provisions of this Act shall come into operation as follows—
(a)
Section 8 shall be deemed to have come into operation on 1 July 1982;
(b)
Sections 1, 2 and 9 shall come into operation on the day on which this Act receives the Royal Assent; and
(c)
The remaining provisions of this Act shall be deemed to have come into operation on 1 July 1983.
The objective of this Act is to ensure that the people of Victoria receive a reasonable rate of return on their equity in certain commercial public authorities of the State.

In this Act—

—
(a)

(b)

where—
A represents the current value of the assets of the public authority as at 30 June immediately preceding that financial year;
B represents that part of the fixed assets that consists of capital work in progress;
C represents the liabilities (whether current or non-current) of the public authority as at that date;
D represents the liabilities incurred to finance capital work in progress; and
E represents that part of the capital liabilities of the public authority as at that date that is in the form of shares held by persons other than the State of Victoria;
Treasurer
means Treasurer of Victoria.

Subject to subsection (3), the value of "A", "B", "C", "D" and "E" in the formulae set out in the interpretation of public equity in subsection (1) shall be determined by the Treasurer after consultation with the Minister responsible for the public authority.

For the purposes of this Act advances or loans made to a public authority out of the Public Account in respect of which a return is being paid to the State of Victoria in the form of interest or in any other form shall not be treated as being part of the public equity of the public authority.

title.emphasis: Annual dividends to be paid by public authorities to Consolidated Fund

legis:body.p: There shall be transferred to the Consolidated Fund in the financial year ending on 30 June 1992 and in each subsequent financial year by each public authority a dividend of such percentage of the public equity of the authority as is determined by the Treasurer after consultation with the Minister responsible for the public authority.

If the Treasurer so determines in any financial year, there shall be transferred to the Consolidated Fund by each public authority, in addition to the dividend payable under subsection (1) in that year, a special dividend of such amount as is determined by the Treasurer after consultation with the Minister responsible for the public authority.

The transfer of a dividend to the Consolidated Fund pursuant to subsection (1) or (1A) shall be made at such times and in such manner as is agreed to by the Treasurer and the public authority or as is in default of such agreement determined by the Governor in Council.

dc:metadata.dc:title: 5 Annual dividends to be paid by public authorities to Consolidated Fund

legis:body.p: Notwithstanding anything in any Act, the financial statements prepared by a public authority in respect of a financial year shall record in such manner as the Treasurer may direct the payment of a dividend required to be transferred to the Consolidated Fund by that public authority in that financial year pursuant to section 5.
The Governor in Council may make regulations for or with respect to any matter or thing required or permitted by this Act to be prescribed or necessary to be prescribed to give effect to this Act.

doc:metadata.currencyStatement: Consolidated as in force on 1 July 2007

legis:body.p: The Public Authorities (Dividends) Act 1983 was assented to on 13 December 1983 and came into operations as follows:

Section 8 was deemed to have come into operation on 1 July 1982: section 2(a); sections 1, 2, 9 on 13 December 1983 section 2(b); rest of Act was deemed to have come into operation on 1 July 1983: section 2(c).
This Version incorporates amendments made to the Public Authorities (Dividends) Act 1983 by Acts and subordinate instruments.
